rComments: Just a lovely a human being. I really enjoyed her lectures, she's so passionate and animated. She seems to truly love what she's doing and love literature. Be prepared to do A LOT of writing during tests/exams, but I found it easy enough to do well.

Im a science student and this was my elective class. I ended up putting in more work than any of my science classes. The final was based on 12 books - the break down of the course was just ridiculous, and she was really patronizing, and a tough marker. The final was brutal. Do not take - it hurt my GPA- should have dropped it when i had the chance
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: She seems like a sweet lady but was not helpful at all in her office hours. Although the readings were very good the lectures were essentially a book club and not really worth it. She is also a very tough grader so if you are looking for an easy class this is not the one for you. I would not recommend her class.

Average. She's a sweet lady, but a surprisingly tough marker! Lectures are boring and kind of useless, but necessary for the final. The reading list for this course was SO long, but easy enough since they are all kids books.

Pretty strange class. We had a debate essay as our midterm on 1 novel, worth 30%. Then we had a standard term essay, worth 40%. Then we had a final exam on the other 12 books (?!?), worth 30%. Lectures are alright, can sometimes be long. Attend lectures for the exams. Professor is very helpful. Thought I was getting B+, got A. That's cool I guess.

Has anybody ever heard of a cumulative final exam where you are not actually tested on any of the material beforehand? Say hello to ENG2111, where we have a 30% final based on TWELVE books. Lectures feel very long and a bit unclear. Extremely unclear on how to study for the ridiculously hard final exam. Better pray you do well on the rest.

The lectures are very long but she makes them interesting. She is really nice and is there if you need help, but I feel she is a hard marker. Make sure you do well on the assignments, as there are not many of them so each one counts for a lot. Also make sure to read every book on the list at least once, it will help a lot.

Professor Hudson is a really good professor overall. Her lectures are long but interesting. Her workshop questions are to make you learn to analyze a book by yourself. Do the questions as she uses them in the final exam! In my opinion, I felt her midterm was way too tough! The final exam was very clear and straightforward.

I enjoyed the course and the content but the lecture were extremely long and seemingly unimportant. She is passionate about what she is teaching but is unclear on what to know. Not only that but she gives you no time to read over the assignment and talk with her about it. Wouldn't take this class with her again.

Class was always dragged on, never felt she was saying anything noteworthy, just her opinions. Loved the reading list and course material, but she didn't teach much and left it up to you with the workshop questions which we would have benefited discussing in class. Expects you to memorize passages for exam essays to use as quotes. Tough exams
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'So many papers']

rComments: I took Children's Literature with her and it was the greatest thing ever. She's this super sweet grandmotherly-type  who reads stories to the class and gives out jam recipes. She's very understanding and very reliable for if you need help in class, and her lectures are fun. 10/10
Although her lectures sometimes feel long she's willing to go out of her way to help her students when necessary! Make time to see her outside of class when you're having trouble!

This prof is my absolute favourite. She gets to know you on a personal level and is so sweet and approachable. If you have a class with her, you are very very lucky! I would take the class all over again if I could! She makes it such a great experience- by far the most enjoyable class I've had!

Prof Hudson is great and I enjoyed the class but the exam was hard! My advice is to do ALL the questions associated with the books assigned - we don't go over them in class but they are absolutely necessary for exam prep.

My favourite professor I've encountered thus far. She is extremely approachable, helpful, and makes material on assignments/exams/essays very clear. She is an energetic lecturer and truly cares that her students do well. Fair work load and fair marker. A real gem of a professor and woman
Very kind professor who will always help if you have questions. Animated and keeps the class interesting!

She's such a mom! Also very passionate and entertaining to listen to because she really gets into it. Very proud of her students when they do well! Only marks in pencil out of respect for her students. Great advice and feedback. Found her a little disorganized, but otherwise enjoyed a class I really wasn't expecting to enjoy!

Her teaching style is interesting but I could see how some might like it. She often talks about how the texts strike her on a personal level & the analysis is largely left up to the students in oral "workshops."  I wasn't a big fan as I felt it wasn't as organized or in-depth as I would have liked. She is a little out in the clouds but very sweet.

Great Professor, really cares about her students. Consistent marker. You really must know what you're talking about. GREAT feedback, also amazing advice about thesis etc. She's by far my favourite professor. She's accommodating, but not a push over. I would highly recommend her to anyone who actually loves English.

Loved her! She's a little quirky, but she loves her subject and is very passionate about what she teaches. Pretty easy class, had her for children's lit. I really liked the option of writing a short story instead of an essay. I would definitely take one of her classes again!

Sweet, whimsical, very knowledgeable about literary circles. Obviously loves teaching and reading Children's Lit. Great reading list and interesting to think of childhood classics critically. The class (and prof) is quirky as it should be and thoroughly enjoyable. :)

Yes, I agree with all the comments that she is a sweet and kind professor. However, I think the workshop component is really a waste of time. We don't learn anything valuable about the works. She does not really provide any critical analysis of texts but rather, goes on and on about the author and how she FEELS about the text. RateB+ to an A- Prof.

A very sweet,and caring prof. Wants her students to do well. However, her choice of readings weren't very good and I don't think you learn much from her lectures. Overall, a good prof and I would recommend her and take her again.

She's darling! And she's also tremendously helpful, and personally supportive of her students. She gives a lot of leeway as far as extensions go, as she'd rather see a good paper than a rush job. Her lectures are great, and she encourages participation through workshops and debate-style midterms. I recommend her strongly.
Fantastic professor! She really does care about your learning and is incredibly understanding and encouraging. I would take any class she teaches. Its absolutely impossible NOT to love her!
She's fantastic!  She's very interested and excited about the material she teaches! You can't help but like her!  I throughly enjoy going to class!

I LOVED her.  The class material might not have been the best but she is really nice to talk to, and she really truly believes that University students aren't there to suffer and sacrifice all else for school.  She's understanding and actually let us bring in baked goods for a little class pot luck, she's so great!

great super fun teacher to have. although i do like the idea of workshops , in practice they never work out as well as i would hope. however, the questiosn in the workshops are quite good to keep in mind so study those. the debate style midterms are AWESOME. if you are relatively intelligent and you can think on your feet you CANT do badly.

She lectures like she's reading a bedtime story. Love the class for the relaxing atmosphere, lol. Wish she'd drop the workshops though, big waste of time - no-one pays attention except when it's their turn to talk & all we have to say are general, vague statements such as "He uses this to build tension". I'd rather hear her honestly :P
Great prof. I would love to have her again because she makes her lectures very interesting and you can see she really enjoys her job and literature. One hell of a prof.

I want her to adopt me. I loved her teaching style, and her explanations. Has the class look at the readings in a workshop fashion- great idea! A little on the kooky side sometimes, but it makes you love her more.  I will take any and all of her classes!!!

awesome teacher--she's really enthusiastic and seems to love what she does which is great and makes it fun and easy to learn--she has high expectations but loves new ideas so never be afraid to speak up in her class!!!
The easiest class ever, and sort of a waste of time. If you want a good mark with the least amount of effort take this class but don't expect to come out any smarter.

Overall the class was Ok...She never takes attendance. She seems ****y on the outside, but I found her quite nice once she got 2 know you. Always willing 2 help out her students... If you are obsessed with chil lit, then take the course, otherwise I don't recommend it cause it is EXTREMELY boring.
She was an awesome prof! made me love the books even more! She has taught this course so many times and everyone loves it!
What a great prof! Really sweet and so enthusiastic about the material.  I loved having her!
Children's Lit: Wonderful way of teaching a class! Very approachable, and had really interesting things to say.  Easy reading - a class for everyone! Couldn't imagine another prof. teaching it.
Really liked her. While the class discussion get tedious sometimes, she's great. Knows what she's talking about and loves it - she's a total mom, but its fun.

Loves Children's Lit. and is an expert on it.  She is not a young prof, yet she conveys a fresh sense of wonder and discovery about the works even to those of us who didn't appreciate them.  If I can, I will take any class she teaches, and so should you!
She was a great teacher to have, very fair.

Great Professor, always had a story of her own and she made the class a pleasure to attend.  The group work was better than listening to a prof talk the whole time.  She got us involved in our education and learning.
A teacher who is very happy to be teaching children's literature. It's nice to see a professor who is always so happy.
She makes Victorian Literature fun! What more colud a student ask for!
Too many  group  presentations...we were there to hear what *she* had to say!
she brilliantly cpativates your mind and soul...a true gem!
No Comments
Her lectures are like stories!  :)  She rocks!
